20/05/2003
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- On Monday (19 May), Greek Foreign Minister George Papandreou submitted a letter to the EU Commission, complaining about Turkish violations of Greek airspace. The letter was addressed to EU Commissioner for Enlargement Gunter Verheugen and lists 965 cases of violation. The issue will be further discussed Tuesday when Greek Defence Minister Yannos Papantoniou meets his Turkish counterpart, Vecdi Gonul, at NATO headquarters in Brussels. (EUobserver - 19/05/03)
